name: Nuestra Señora De La Candelaria Parish
details: The church is known for its 126 steps connecting the local road to the main church on top of the hill.It has a Spanish style façade. Due to natural calamities and war, only the belfry connected to the church is the remaining original structure of the original 1618 church.

name: San Sebastian Parish Church
details: First stone church in Laguna and the first Franciscan building outside Manila made out of stone.

name: Saint John the Baptist Parish
details: Catholic Church venerating St. John the Baptist, popular tourist destination during Holy Week

name: Cathedral of Our Lady of Maulawin
details: Catholic Church venerating the Lady of Mulauwin, popular tourist destination during Holy Week

name: Emilio Jacinto Burial Place and Monument
details: The monument for Emilio Jacinto in Himlayang Pilipino was created by the sculptor Florante Caedo and unveiled on December 15, 1976.

name: Immaculate Conception Parish Church
details: Well-known Church venerating the Virgin Mary, established at the year 1602, and was burned during the 1945 Philippine Campaign of WWII

name: Labanan sa Maimpis
details: Memorial for the Battle between the Spanish force and the Katipuneros of Laguna led by General Emilio Jacinto, 27 February 1898

name: St. Gregory the Great Parish Church
details: One of the oldest Roman Catholic churches in the Philippines located in the municipality of Majayjay in Laguna

name: Puente del Capricho
details: Puente de Capriccio was initiated by Spanish franciscan priest Victoriano del Moral. The bridge symbolizes the defiance of Filipino workers against the oppressive Spanish colonialists during the colonial period.

name: Jose Rizal Monument
details: It is believed that the monument of Rizal in Majayjay was built on the year 1904, eight years after his execution in Bagumbayan, Manila (now Rizal / Luneta Park) on December 30, 1896. The construction of the monument was done under the auspices of Municipal President (Mayor) Don Antonio Escobar (1904-1905). Rizal’s death day can be seen on the side of its monument stairs.

name: The Roman Catholic Parish of San Santiago Apostol
details: The main attraction of the church is the original ceiling mural done by the famous painter Simón Flores (1839–1904). Not to be missed are his original painting of the Holy Family, the artesian well (dug in the 1800s) in the patio – the first well in the country to be so situated, and the rare betis tree nearby donated by sociologist Randy David, a native of the town. A two-minute walk from the church is the restored David House, ancestral home of the sociologist, which they christened as Bale Pinauid or Bahay Pawid.

name: Three Crosses of Paete
details: The Tatlong Krus are three crosses on the peak of mount Humarap, part of the mountain of Sierra Madre located in Paete, in the province of Laguna, along the northeastern coast of Luzon island in the Philippines. The Three Crosses started out with three wooden crosses and now are made of concrete

name: Diocesan Shrine and Parish of Our Lady of Guadalupe
details: Our Lady of Guadalupe Parish Church, designated as the Diocesan Shrine of Our Lady of Guadalupe of the Roman Catholic Diocese of San Pablo, is the only Roman Catholic church in Pagsanjan, Laguna, Philippines, and the oldest church in the Philippines under the patronage of Our Lady of Guadalupe.

name: Saint Peter of Alcantara Parish Church
details: The St. Peter of Alcantara Parish Church, designated as the Diocesan Shrine of Nuestra Señora de los Dolores de Turumba, is a Roman Catholic church in Pakil, Laguna, Philippines. It enshrines the Our Lady of Turumba painting.

name: Nuestra Senora dela Natividad Parish
details: The Nuestra Señora dela Natividad Parish, commonly known as Pangil Church, is a Roman Catholic church in Natividad, Pangil, Laguna, Philippines. The statue of the pregnant Virgin Mary is said to be a gift from King Carlos III of Spain

name: National Shrine and Parish of San Antonio
details: Has the 4th Oldest Surviving Bell in the Phillipines, and is the First Antonine Church in the Philippines

name: Aguinaldo Shrine (Museo ni Emilio Aguinaldo)
details: Contains the historical memorabilia and interred remains of the First Philippine President, Emilio Aguinaldo

name: Minor Basilica of St. Michael the Archangel
details: The influence of Chinese architecture in Tayabas is pronounced in the design of the basilica. Stone lions in front of the building show a link to the presence of Chinese traders before the Spanish colonial era.

name: Manuel Quezon Monument

name: Malabrigo Lighthouse
details: Completed and lit in 1896, it is one of the oldest working lighthouses in the Philippines as well as the best preserved lighthouse in the country. It serves as a guide for ships passing through the Verde Island Passage going to either Batangas Bay or Sibuyan Sea.

name: Antipolo Cathedral

name: Pagsanjan Falls
details: Pagsanjan Falls, also known as Cavinti Falls, is one of the most famous waterfalls in the Philippines. Located in the province of Laguna, the falls is one of the major tourist attractions of the region.

name: Cavinti Underground River and Caves Complex
details: The caves complex offers cave chambers that are friendly to explore even for beginners as well as challenging ones for the more advanced cave explorers.

name: Nakulo Falls
details: One of the waterfalls attractions in Cavinti which is accessible via The Cliff Eco-Sanctuary Resort in Brgy. Anglas. The trail is only a 10-minute walkway to its final stretch at the steeply angled metal ladder.

name: Bumbungan Eco Park
details: Bumbungan was dammed at this section where the top of the spillway also served as a wet bridge on the Lumban-Caliraya-Cavinti Road. After an adjacent bridge was constructed, the dam and adjacent land became the Eco-Park with huts for picnickers and bathroom facilities.

name: Bumbungan Twin Falls
details: This trail is great for hiking and walking, and it's unlikely you'll encounter many other people while exploring. The trail is open year-round and is beautiful to visit anytime.

name: Tanawan View Deck

name: Hulugan Falls
details: Towering at around 70 meters in height, Hulugan falls was a wonderful sight to behold on that early morning. They said that the name Hulugan came to be because back in the days, there were a lot of water buffalos that fell or nahulog there, thus the name.

name: Hulugan Falls Jump-off Point

name: Hidden Falls

name: Pililla 54 MW Windmill

name: Balete Tree of Mabitac (Century Tree)

name: Bayside Baywalk

name: Taytay Falls
details: Taytay Falls, also called Imelda Falls, is one of the favorite waterfall destinations in Laguna. It has a height of 10-15 meters and releases pristine, icy cold spring waters coming from Mount Banahaw. According to history, it was named after the ex-First Lady Imelda Marcos who funded the promotion of tourism of this spot.

The Taal Volcano itself has a lake of its own inside its crater called 'Crater Lake'.
